topic for her.

83
00:04:15,500 --> 00:04:17,166
Wanna grab some dessert, too?

84
00:04:17,250 --> 00:04:19,291
What? You mean it, really?

85
00:04:19,375 --> 00:04:20,416
Sure, what d'ya want?

86
00:04:20,500 --> 00:04:23,208
I would like to have
an éclair, please!

87
00:04:23,291 --> 00:04:25,750
Did you know that the word
"éclair" translates to

88
00:04:25,833 --> 00:04:26,916
"flash of lightning"?

89
00:04:27,000 --> 00:04:28,166
[KOBAYASHI]
I did not.

90
00:04:28,250 --> 00:04:30,416
Speaking of lightning,
talk to me about Thor.

91
00:04:30,500 --> 00:04:32,416
Is your name related to his?

92
00:04:32,500 --> 00:04:35,708
Absolutely not! It comes from
an author in this world.

93
00:04:35,791 --> 00:04:38,166
At least that's what my
parents have always told me.

94
00:04:38,250 --> 00:04:40,000
Right. Of course
you have parents.

95
00:04:40,083 --> 00:04:41,750
