150
00:07:40,583 --> 00:07:41,791
--Break up with her, slut!
--Whoa-kay!

151
00:07:41,875 --> 00:07:43,416
--Give her back!
--[grunts] Okay! Ow!

152
00:07:43,500 --> 00:07:45,166
--I'll kill you!
--Miss Kobayashi, I'm home--

153
00:07:45,250 --> 00:07:46,291
[KOBAYASHI gasps]

154
00:07:47,333 --> 00:07:48,333
[TOHRU snarls]

155
00:07:48,416 --> 00:07:52,041
Miss Kobayashi,
are you cheating on me?!

156
00:07:52,125 --> 00:07:54,291
This is already weird,
don't make it worse.

157
00:07:54,375 --> 00:07:55,750
Lady Tohru.

158
00:07:55,833 --> 00:07:56,875
[gasps]

159
00:07:58,750 --> 00:08:00,375
[TOHRU]
This girl is Kanna Kamui.

160
00:08:00,458 --> 00:08:02,375
She's an acquaintance of mine.

161
00:08:02,458 --> 00:08:03,500
Figured as much.

162
00:08:03,583 --> 00:08:05,416
Lady Tohru
completely disappeared,

163
00:08:05,500 --> 00:08:06,791
so I came to find her.

164
00:08:06,875 --> 00:08:08,250
Completely disappeared?

165
00:08:08,333 --> 00:08:10,500
Tohru, you should
communicate with your friends

166
00:08:10,583 --> 00:08:11,541
better than that.

167
00:08:11,625 --> 00:08:13,375
I know.

168
00:08:13,458 --> 00:08:15,791
I'm surprised you found
this place, Kanna.

169
00:08:15,875 --> 00:08:18,916
I saw you breathe fire
on those clouds the other day.

170
00:08:19,000 --> 00:08:21,291
--And I sensed your magic.
--[TOHRU] Right...

171
00:08:21,375 --> 00:08:23,291
[KOBAYASHI] It's almost like you
shouldn't have done that.

172
00:08:23,375 --> 00:08:26,833
Lady Tohru, why are you
dressed in such an odd outfit?

173
00:08:26,916 --> 00:08:28,916
Will you please
come back home with me?

174
00:08:29,000 --> 00:08:31,041
I need you, Lady Tohru.

175
00:08:31,125 --> 00:08:32,166
[TOHRU sighs]

176
00:08:35,625 --> 00:08:37,250
[TOHRU]
I'm not going home.

177
00:08:37,333 --> 00:08:40,208
[gasps]
But why not?

178
00:08:40,291 --> 00:08:41,750
Why?

179
00:08:41,833 --> 00:08:44,083
Because I'm in love
with Miss Kobayashi!

180
00:08:44,166 --> 00:08:45,083
Be serious.

181
00:08:45,166 --> 00:08:46,583
--I knew it!
--[KOBAYASHI] What?!

182
00:08:46,666 --> 00:08:49,333
I saw you on your
little date at the bazaar!

183
00:08:49,416 --> 00:08:52,791
Holding each other's hands
in public. You perverts!

184
00:08:52,875 --> 00:08:53,958
[KOBAYASHI]
I'm sorry, what?

185
00:08:54,041 --> 00:08:55,000
[TOHRU chuckles]

186
00:08:55,083 --> 00:08:56,208
[KOBAYASHI]
Why are you blushing?!

187
00:08:56,291 --> 00:08:58,291
You should know,
if I must, I will kill you.

188
00:08:58,375 --> 00:08:59,916
[gasps]

189
00:09:00,000 --> 00:09:01,708
Now, die!

190
00:09:01,791 --> 00:09:04,416
[grunting]

191
00:09:04,500 --> 00:09:06,541
[pants]

192
00:09:06,625 --> 00:09:08,083
[grunts]

193
00:09:08,166 --> 00:09:11,541
Kanna. What happened to you?
You're practically powerless.

194
00:09:11,625 --> 00:09:14,666
Your power's special
here, Lady Tohru!

195
00:09:14,750 --> 00:09:17,250
The mana purity
is too low for me!

196
00:09:17,333 --> 00:09:20,375
[KOBAYASHI] Kanna, does that
mean... you can't get home?

197
00:09:20,458 --> 00:09:21,250
[KANNA gasps]

198
00:09:21,333 --> 00:09:23,333
No. That's not true, shut up.

199
00:09:23,416 --> 00:09:26,083
All right. Well, can I ask,
do you have anywhere to stay?

200
00:09:26,166 --> 00:09:27,625
[KANNA gasps]

201
00:09:27,708 --> 00:09:29,500
[KOBAYASHI] Tohru, look me in
the eye and answer for her.

202
00:09:29,583 --> 00:09:31,166
[TOHRU] I can't.
Your dead-fish eyes scare me,

203
00:09:31,250 --> 00:09:33,333
Miss Kobayashi.

204
00:09:33,416 --> 00:09:36,041
Kanna, please tell us
honestly what you're planning.

205
00:09:36,125 --> 00:09:37,375
It's okay.

206
00:09:37,458 --> 00:09:39,625
But if you're after
Miss Kobayashi for yourself,

207
00:09:39,708 --> 00:09:42,458
--you need to give that up--
--Tohru, shut up for a second.

208
00:09:45,125 --> 00:09:48,875
[KANNA whines]
Actually...

209
00:09:48,958 --> 00:09:51,458
You were exiled
for a stupid prank?

210
00:09:51,541 --> 00:09:53,875
[TOHRU] Kanna always has
loved practical jokes.

211
00:09:53,958 --> 00:09:55,916
[KOBAYASHI]
Okay, so long story short...

212
00:09:56,000 --> 00:09:57,166
--It's like this?
--[BOY B] I'll be good!

213
00:09:57,250 --> 00:09:58,625
--Yes, it's like that.
--Mommy, open up!

214
00:09:58,708 --> 00:10:01,166
I'm sure they want her to
reflect on her actions.

215
00:10:01,250 --> 00:10:03,750
It would be useless for me
to send her back.

216
00:10:03,833 --> 00:10:06,500
[KOBAYASHI] So right now,
she's all on her own.

217
00:10:06,583 --> 00:10:07,625
[TOHRU]
Yes...

218
00:10:13,875 --> 00:10:14,916
[KOBAYASHI]
Kanna?

219
00:10:17,500 --> 00:10:19,583
Do you wanna stay here
with the two of us?

220
00:10:19,666 --> 00:10:21,166
[gasps]

221
00:10:21,250 --> 00:10:22,750
Hold on.

222
00:10:22,833 --> 00:10:25,666
Why'd it take you so much longer
to decide to let me stay, huh?

223
00:10:25,750 --> 00:10:28,166
Once you're stuck with one,
you might as well have two.

224
00:10:28,250 --> 00:10:30,791
Tch! I don't trust
you humans, though!

225
00:10:30,875 --> 00:10:32,541
You must be plotting something!

226
00:10:32,625 --> 00:10:35,541
You just wanna use me!

227
00:10:35,625 --> 00:10:36,666
[gasps]

228
00:10:38,375 --> 00:10:41,125
You can't trust anyone
in an unknown world?

229
00:10:41,208 --> 00:10:43,250
Hey, that makes sense to me.

230
00:10:43,333 --> 00:10:46,000
I wouldn't trust anyone, either.

231
00:10:46,083 --> 00:10:48,791
I think a person
has to earn trust.

232
00:10:48,875 --> 00:10:50,750
And that can only happen
after you become friends

233
00:10:50,833 --> 00:10:53,583
or get, like,
"romantically" involved.

234
00:10:53,666 --> 00:10:55,291
[KANNA whines]

235
00:10:55,375 --> 00:10:59,458
Listen, Kanna. I'm not asking
for your trust or friendship.

236
00:10:59,541 --> 00:11:01,916
You can live here. That's all.

237
00:11:03,541 --> 00:11:09,583
[KANNA whimpers]

238
00:11:09,666 --> 00:11:11,125
Okay...

239
00:11:11,208 --> 00:11:14,750
--[KOBAYASHI chuckles]
--[KANNA sobs quietly]

240
00:11:14,833 --> 00:11:16,583
[TOHRU]
She's so good.

241
00:11:16,666 --> 00:11:19,666
I'm so glad I fell in love
with Miss Kobayashi.

242
00:11:37,208 --> 00:11:38,458
[KOBAYASHI]
There!

243
00:11:38,541 --> 00:11:39,833
There! There!

244
00:11:39,916 --> 00:11:41,541
Here!

245
00:11:41,625 --> 00:11:43,166
[KOBAYASHI]
How to tame your dragon.

246
00:11:51,916 --> 00:11:54,083
[KANNA]
Shoop!

247
00:11:55,458 --> 00:11:57,125
I want to play!

248
00:11:57,208 --> 00:11:58,375
But the game?

249
00:11:58,458 --> 00:11:59,625
[KANNA]
Yeah, I'm bored with that.

250
00:11:59,708 --> 00:12:01,500
Remember, Kanna's still a child.

251
00:12:01,583 --> 00:12:04,625
She craves physical
exercise to the fullest!

252
00:12:04,708 --> 00:12:06,000
[KOBAYASHI]
What's wrong with video games?

253
00:12:06,083 --> 00:12:08,750
When I was a kid, that's how
I spent all of my time.

254
00:12:08,833 --> 00:12:11,625
Kanna, would you like to go
play outside with me today?

255
00:12:11,708 --> 00:12:14,500
[KANNA]
Mm! Yeah!

256
00:12:14,583 --> 00:12:16,333
Care to join, Miss Kobayashi?

257
00:12:16,416 --> 00:12:17,916
Yes! Please join us!

258
00:12:18,000 --> 00:12:19,166
I don't exercise.

259
00:12:19,250 --> 00:12:21,166
[screams]

260
00:12:28,083 --> 00:12:29,500
And we're... where?

261
00:12:29,583 --> 00:12:31,041
I dunno.

262
00:12:31,125 --> 00:12:33,583
I landed in the first big field
I saw that looked pleasant.

263
00:12:34,541 --> 00:12:37,333
Well, whatever works.

264
00:12:37,416 --> 00:12:40,333
I'll be here sleeping off
the fatigue from my deathma.

265
00:12:40,416 --> 00:12:42,166
Wake me up when
we're finished playing.

266
00:12:42,250 --> 00:12:44,333
Then, figure out
how to get us home.

267
00:12:44,416 --> 00:12:46,250
All right, if that's
what you want.

268
00:12:46,333 --> 00:12:48,458
You ready to play even
if it's just the two of us?

269
00:12:48,541 --> 00:12:49,583
[KANNA]
Mm!

270
00:12:53,541 --> 00:12:55,250
[KOBAYASHI yelps, gasps]

271
00:12:57,458 --> 00:12:59,541
[BOTH grunt]

272
00:13:09,750 --> 00:13:10,791
Tch!

273
00:13:12,875 --> 00:13:13,916
[KANNA gasps]

274
00:13:20,333 --> 00:13:21,625
Wait! Wait, wait!

275
00:13:21,708 --> 00:13:23,500
Oh, hey. I thought
you were gonna take a nap?

276
00:13:23,583 --> 00:13:25,208
[KOBAYASHI] How can I sleep
when you two are trying

277
00:13:25,291 --> 00:13:26,791
to kill each other?!

278
00:13:26,875 --> 00:13:29,875
Don't be silly-- we were only
roughhousing a teeny-tiny bit.

279
00:13:29,958 --> 00:13:31,375
You over-exaggerate.

280
00:13:31,458 --> 00:13:33,125
[KOBAYASHI] Shoot,
I'm at the disadvantage now.

281
00:13:33,208 --> 00:13:36,416
Oh! I bet you wanted to join in,
too, right, Miss Kobayashi?

282
00:13:36,500 --> 00:13:38,125
Shame! You should
be more honest!

283
00:13:38,208 --> 00:13:39,625
[KOBAYASHI]
You'd kill me!

284
00:13:39,708 --> 00:13:43,791
[KANNA groans] It's fun to
move around in a human body.

285
00:13:43,875 --> 00:13:45,125
What happened with you, Kanna?

286
00:13:45,208 --> 00:13:47,291
I thought your strength
had been depleted somehow.

287
00:13:47,375 --> 00:13:50,375
It had been, but the source
of my power is electricity.

288
00:13:50,458 --> 00:13:52,416
It returned after I recharged.

289
00:13:52,500 --> 00:13:54,541
So what, you're made of lithium?

290
00:13:54,625 --> 00:13:56,791
If you're playing,
keep it to human standards.

291
00:13:56,875 --> 00:13:59,416
What? We were at
human standards.

292
00:13:59,500 --> 00:14:01,291
--Huh?
--Huh?

293
00:14:01,375 --> 00:14:03,500
In our world there are
plenty of humans capable

294
00:14:03,583 --> 00:14:05,041
of doing this kind of thing.

295
00:14:05,125 --> 00:14:07,625
[KOBAYASHI] There's very few
who can do it here, like, none.

296
00:14:07,708 --> 00:14:10,291
[TOHRU] That's not true, I saw
some on TV the other day.

297
00:14:10,375 --> 00:14:12,625
[KOBAYASHI] What you saw
was fiction, not reality.

298
00:14:12,708 --> 00:14:13,625
--[BOTH gasp]
--[KOBAYASHI] Oh.

299
00:14:13,708 --> 00:14:16,583
Sorry, for crushing your dreams.

300
00:14:16,666 --> 00:14:19,875
Whatever. I'll be
sleeping in this spot.

301
00:14:19,958 --> 00:14:22,375
Try to keep your playing
around my level.

302
00:14:22,458 --> 00:14:25,000
Sure! Well, there
you have it, Kanna.

303
00:14:25,083 --> 00:14:28,750
Let's start by recalling exactly
how Miss Kobayashi usually acts.

304
00:14:28,833 --> 00:14:30,250
[KANNA]
Okay!

305
00:14:31,083 --> 00:14:33,291
[KOBAYASHI]
The power of dragons.

306
00:14:33,375 --> 00:14:37,041
I've seen it a few times now,
but it's still terrifying.

307
00:14:37,125 --> 00:14:40,083
If they wanted to,
this world would be gone.

308
00:14:48,000 --> 00:14:50,833
[TOHRU]
My lower back! It's killing me!

309
00:14:50,916 --> 00:14:53,791
[KANNA]
I'm tired... I'm gonna die...

310
00:14:55,125 --> 00:14:58,166
[KOBAYASHI] Yeah, never mind.
They'd never destroy our world.

311
00:14:58,250 --> 00:15:02,375
And, for the record,
they've both totally nailed me.

312
00:15:02,458 --> 00:15:04,333
[TOHRU]
Ah, that was super fun.

313
00:15:04,416 --> 00:15:05,750
Was it?

314
00:15:05,833 --> 00:15:08,666
I suppose you really didn't want
to play, Miss Kobayashi.

315
00:15:08,750 --> 00:15:09,791
[KOBAYASHI]
Hmph.

316
00:15:26,083 --> 00:15:27,750
I don't mind playing Word Chain.

317
00:15:27,833 --> 00:15:28,708
Indigo.

318
00:15:28,791 --> 00:15:29,708
Gorilla.

319
00:15:29,791 --> 00:15:30,833
Lambskin.

320
00:15:30,916 --> 00:15:32,166
Intercom.

321
00:15:32,250 --> 00:15:33,708
[KANNA]
Compadre.

322
00:15:33,791 --> 00:15:36,041
[TOHRU]
Dre... Dre...

323
00:15:37,541 --> 00:15:38,791
[TOHRU]
Oh, dragon!

324
00:15:38,875 --> 00:15:40,208
[KOBAYASHI]
Ha, ha, you lose.

325
00:15:40,291 --> 00:15:42,666
[TOHRU]
Agh! [laughs]

326
00:15:50,166 --> 00:15:51,125
[KOBAYASHI grunts]

327
00:15:51,208 --> 00:15:53,000
[TOHRU]
Ah! You're being rude.

328
00:15:53,083 --> 00:15:55,291
you only left my
tail-meat behind again!

329
00:15:55,375 --> 00:15:57,250
I said I was ethically opposed.

330
00:15:57,333 --> 00:15:59,083
Although, if you turned
it into ground meat,

331
00:15:59,166 --> 00:16:00,416
I probably wouldn't notice.

332
00:16:00,500 --> 00:16:02,000
But then you would
have no way of knowing

333
00:16:02,083 --> 00:16:03,666
it was specifically my meat.

334
00:16:03,750 --> 00:16:05,708
Why is that so important to you?

335
00:16:10,500 --> 00:16:12,583
--[KOBAYASHI] Hmm?
--Miss Kobayashi...

336
00:16:12,666 --> 00:16:14,750
Please don't enter or
even peek into the kitchen

337
00:16:14,833 --> 00:16:16,875
until I call for you, okay?

338
00:16:16,958 --> 00:16:18,000
Thank you...

339
00:16:19,208 --> 00:16:20,291
Hey!

340
00:16:20,375 --> 00:16:21,250
[KOBAYASHI]
I will never want your tail!

341
00:16:21,333 --> 00:16:22,416
[screams]

342
00:16:25,416 --> 00:16:27,916
[KANNA]
Where are you going, Kobayashi?

343
00:16:28,000 --> 00:16:28,916
[KOBAYASHI]
Hmm? To work.

344
00:16:29,000 --> 00:16:30,666
I wanna go with you.

345
00:16:30,750 --> 00:16:33,875
Kanna, you have things to do
with me today, remember?

346
00:16:33,958 --> 00:16:35,333
[KOBAYASHI]
Things like what?

347
00:16:35,416 --> 00:16:38,291
[TOHRU] Kanna hasn't been in
this world for very long.

348
00:16:38,375 --> 00:16:40,666
I thought it would be good for
me to teach her some basics.

349
00:16:40,750 --> 00:16:42,250
Yeah? You thought that?

350
00:16:42,333 --> 00:16:46,208
No way! I want Kobayashi!

351
00:16:46,291 --> 00:16:47,583
This came out of nowhere.

352
00:16:47,666 --> 00:16:50,166
If you keep being selfish,
I'll break you.

353
00:16:50,250 --> 00:16:52,083
--[KOBAYASHI] I'm off!
--[TOHRU] Safe travels!

354
00:16:53,125 --> 00:16:54,708
Now then. It's time
for you to learn

355
00:16:54,791 --> 00:16:56,541
common sense for this world.

356
00:16:56,625 --> 00:16:58,416
[KANNA]
What kind of common sense?

357
00:16:58,500 --> 00:17:01,250
[TOHRU] To start with, you need
to learn what you must not do.

358
00:17:01,333 --> 00:17:03,000
Oh!

359
00:17:03,083 --> 00:17:05,041
[TOHRU] Honor traffic
lights at all times!

360
00:17:05,125 --> 00:17:07,333
Otherwise, you'll be
squashed by a "car."

361
00:17:07,416 --> 00:17:09,791
[KANNA] That's what those
iron boxes are called?

362
00:17:09,875 --> 00:17:11,333
Lady Tohru, you're smart!

363
00:17:11,416 --> 00:17:12,333
[TOHRU chuckles]

364
00:17:12,416 --> 00:17:14,125
[KANNA]
How do they move around?

365
00:17:15,458 --> 00:17:16,916
[TOHRU]
Probably with magic.

366
00:17:17,000 --> 00:17:19,958
Apparently, you need a device
called a "license" for them.

367
00:17:20,041 --> 00:17:21,541
Does Kobayashi have that?

368
00:17:21,625 --> 00:17:24,041
A license?
I'd love to ride in a car!

369
00:17:24,125 --> 00:17:26,375
[TOHRU] From what I understand,
she possesses a license,

370
00:17:26,458 --> 00:17:28,250
but she does not have a car.

371
00:17:28,333 --> 00:17:30,375
Cars impose strains
called "inspections,"

372
00:17:30,458 --> 00:17:31,875
"loans," and "tires."

373
00:17:31,958 --> 00:17:35,125
[KANNA] It seems power comes
at a price in every world.

374
00:17:35,208 --> 00:17:39,000
But... wouldn't it be easier
if she just had you carry her?

375
00:17:39,083 --> 00:17:41,375
Why doesn't Kobayashi do that?

376
00:17:41,458 --> 00:17:43,250
Great question.

377
00:17:43,333 --> 00:17:45,958
[TAKIYA] Wow, you've got
another relative with you?

378
00:17:46,041 --> 00:17:47,333
This one a maid, too?

379
00:17:47,416 --> 00:17:52,500
Gothic Lolita. A Gothic Lolita
with a tribal theme.

380
00:17:52,583 --> 00:17:55,000
Huh, interesting twist.

381
00:17:55,083 --> 00:17:56,958
[KOBAYASHI] Tohru said she was
gonna teach her some things,

382
00:17:57,041 --> 00:17:58,583
so I'm a little worried.

383
00:17:58,666 --> 00:18:01,416
[TAKIYA] Why? Tohru seems
to have her act together.

384
00:18:01,500 --> 00:18:03,208
You think so?

385
00:18:03,291 --> 00:18:05,625
Well, at the very least,
I'm confident she has

386
00:18:05,708 --> 00:18:07,416
compassion for her friends.

387
00:18:07,500 --> 00:18:10,750
For real? That is hilarious.
Are you serious?

388
00:18:10,833 --> 00:18:11,750
[KANNA]
What's he saying?

389
00:18:11,833 --> 00:18:13,125
[TOHRU]
Magic words.

390
00:18:13,208 --> 00:18:15,041
You can get through
most conversations using

391
00:18:15,125 --> 00:18:16,791
those phrases,
so try to remember them.

392
00:18:16,875 --> 00:18:19,250
[BOYS AND GIRLS
laughing, chatting]

393
00:18:19,333 --> 00:18:21,333
What's that thing?

394
00:18:21,416 --> 00:18:22,583
[TOHRU]
I don't know.

395
00:18:22,666 --> 00:18:25,083
A tool children play with?
How do they play?

396
00:18:25,166 --> 00:18:27,750
It looks like it uses
the principle of levers, but...

397
00:18:27,833 --> 00:18:30,875
[gasps] That's a training
device for catapults!

398
00:18:30,958 --> 00:18:32,500
[KANNA]
Oh!

399
00:18:32,583 --> 00:18:34,625
[TOHRU] This is how human
children learn the means

400
00:18:34,708 --> 00:18:36,875
of combating monsters
in the sky!

401
00:18:36,958 --> 00:18:38,666
[KANNA]
Ooh!

402
00:18:38,750 --> 00:18:39,916
[DRAGON A roars]

403
00:18:40,000 --> 00:18:40,750
What's that?

404
00:18:40,833 --> 00:18:42,416
That's called a crepe stand.

405
00:18:46,250 --> 00:18:49,666
It's sweet, like the
eggs of a yatagarasu.

406
00:18:49,750 --> 00:18:50,541
What's that?

407
00:18:50,625 --> 00:18:52,500
Oh, that's an ice cream stand!

408
00:18:55,958 --> 00:18:58,291
It's cold. But yummy!

409
00:19:02,958 --> 00:19:04,583
[KANNA]
This world is peaceful.

410
00:19:04,666 --> 00:19:07,083
[TOHRU]
It is, isn't it?

411
00:19:07,166 --> 00:19:10,041
Are there dragons here?
Other than visitors.

412
00:19:10,125 --> 00:19:11,541
[TOHRU]
No, it seems there aren't.

413
00:19:11,625 --> 00:19:15,208
I don't know if they went
extinct or if they moved away.

414
00:19:15,291 --> 00:19:17,500
[KANNA] Is it bad to
revert to my original form?

415
00:19:17,583 --> 00:19:19,250
[TOHRU] No, not as long
as you don't allow

416
00:19:19,333 --> 00:19:21,458
that form to be seen.

417
00:19:21,541 --> 00:19:24,333
Have you learned how to use
perception blocking yet, Kanna?

418
00:19:24,416 --> 00:19:25,666
Not yet.

419
00:19:25,750 --> 00:19:29,000
That's okay. Besides,
it's not like there's ever

420
00:19:29,083 --> 00:19:31,458
any real need for it anyways.

421
00:19:31,541 --> 00:19:33,833
Uh. Um, Lady Tohru?

422
00:19:33,916 --> 00:19:35,166
Yes, ma'am?

423
00:19:35,250 --> 00:19:37,666
[KANNA] Why did you decide
to come to this world?

424
00:19:40,041 --> 00:19:41,583
[TOHRU sighs]

425
00:19:41,666 --> 00:19:45,333
All the rumors I heard
said that you died.

426
00:19:45,416 --> 00:19:47,833
I was happy to find out
they were wrong.

427
00:19:47,916 --> 00:19:48,875
Well, to be honest,

428
00:19:48,958 --> 00:19:51,583
I came to this world
just to escape.

429
00:19:51,666 --> 00:19:53,541
I was on the verge
of death when I got here,

430
00:19:53,625 --> 00:19:56,000
but Miss Kobayashi saved me.

431
00:19:56,083 --> 00:19:57,750
Kobayashi?

432
00:19:57,833 --> 00:20:01,333
I decided to repay her by being
her personal, live-in maid.

433
00:20:01,416 --> 00:20:04,166
Meanwhile, I let people
think I was dead.

434
00:20:04,250 --> 00:20:07,333
I've only told a handful
of dragons about my survival.

435
00:20:07,416 --> 00:20:09,875
Like Miss Lucoah
and Mister Fafnir.

436
00:20:09,958 --> 00:20:12,250
That's neat, you kinda
sound like a retiree.

437
00:20:12,333 --> 00:20:15,083
[chuckles]
I guess I kinda am.

438
00:20:16,708 --> 00:20:18,250
You know what's funny, Kanna?

439
00:20:23,416 --> 00:20:26,750
[TOHRU] I'm very happy.
Right in this moment.

440
00:20:26,833 --> 00:20:28,541
[KANNA]
Hmm.

441
00:20:28,625 --> 00:20:29,916
[TOHRU]
Come on, Kanna!

442
00:20:30,000 --> 00:20:32,416
There's gotta be more stuff
you want to know about!

443
00:20:32,500 --> 00:20:33,541
[KANNA]
Hmm.

444
00:20:36,791 --> 00:20:39,083
I'd like to see
Kobayashi's work.

445
00:20:39,166 --> 00:20:42,208
Uh. She might get mad at you.

446
00:20:42,291 --> 00:20:44,041
[KANNA]
So what? I wanna see.

447
00:20:44,125 --> 00:20:46,333
[TOHRU]
Hmm. Well, all right.

448
00:20:46,416 --> 00:20:48,250
Let's go say hello to her, then.

449
00:20:59,416 --> 00:21:02,125
[TOHRU] Feel free to change.
I blocked perception of us.

450
00:21:02,208 --> 00:21:03,250
[KANNA]
Mm.

451
00:21:14,875 --> 00:21:16,833
[KOBAYASHI groans]

452
00:21:21,166 --> 00:21:21,791
[gasps]

453
00:21:21,875 --> 00:21:22,916
What's wrong with you?

454
00:21:23,000 --> 00:21:25,541
[KOBAYASHI]
Huh? Oh, nothing's wrong.

455
00:21:31,000 --> 00:21:32,541
[KOBAYASHI]
Whatever.

456
00:21:43,333 --> 00:21:45,250
It's not practice for catapults?

457
00:21:45,333 --> 00:21:47,750
It's not. Just a
toy kids play on.

458
00:21:47,833 --> 00:21:49,666
How about that.

459
00:21:49,750 --> 00:21:52,583
[giggles]

460
00:21:52,666 --> 00:21:55,250
[KANNA]
Whoa.

461
00:21:55,333 --> 00:21:56,750
Whoa, this is fun!

462
00:21:56,833 --> 00:21:58,166
Yeah.

463
00:21:58,250 --> 00:21:59,875
[TOHRU]
This toy is great!

464
00:21:59,958 --> 00:22:01,541
Glad it makes you happy.

465
00:23:33,416 --> 00:23:35,791
[TOHRU] Kanna, supposedly
there are myriads of gods

466
00:23:35,875 --> 00:23:37,083
living in this world.

467
00:23:37,166 --> 00:23:39,000
[KANNA] Lady Tohru,
what does "myriads" mean?

468
00:23:39,083 --> 00:23:41,625
[TOHRU] Basically, gods reside
in all kinds of things here.

469
00:23:41,708 --> 00:23:43,083
[KANNA]
Whoa, that's scary.

470
00:23:43,166 --> 00:23:44,333
[TOHRU]
Don't let your guard down.

471
00:23:44,416 --> 00:23:45,458
[KANNA]
Right.

